Harry L. Rattenberry https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_L._Rattenberry 0 Harry L. Rattenberry (December 14, 1857 – December 9, 1925) was an American film actor. He appeared in 129 films between 1913 and 1925. He was born in Sacramento, California and died in Los Angeles, California. His parents were William Henry Rattenberry (1834-1889) and Mary Ann Broomhead (c. 1829-1909), a former wife of notable Mormon missionary Cyrus H. Wheelock.
